## §2. AUDIT BYPASS — 3 HASH CONFLICT (PARTIAL_CLOSED)

### §2.1 Original threat (per session 20260417)

3 conflicting hash algorithms used cross codebase:
- Math.imul (placeholder, not cryptographic)
- SHA-256 (real)
- btoa (base64 encoding, not hash)

Risk: audit chain integrity unverifiable when validators disagree on hash algo.

### §2.2 Fix applied

Commit 7f4d297 (session 20260417): standardize to SHA-256 via crypto.createHash('sha256').

### §2.3 Ground truth post-fix (scan 2026-04-24)

**SHA-256 real implementation: 87 files**

Top kernel/core implementations:
- `src/core/ingestion/utils.ts` — `crypto.subtle.digest('SHA-256', msgBuffer)`
- `src/cells/kernel/audit-cell/domain/engines/blockchain-shard.engine.ts` — `createHash("sha256").update(str).digest("hex")`
- `src/cells/kernel/audit-cell/domain/services/auditchainservice.ts` — `createHash("sha256")`
- `src/cells/kernel/audit-cell/domain/services/audit-writer.service.ts` — Web Crypto API real
- `src/governance/moments/registry.ts` — `computeSirasign — canonical JSON serialize then SHA-256`

### §2.4 Math.imul mentions remaining (13 files, deep review)

#### §2.4.1 CONFIRMED PLACEHOLDER (per session 20260414 deep scan)

3 files documented as REAL ARCHITECTURE with placeholder hash, ready for crypto provider swap:

| File | Line | Pattern | Memory ref |
|---|---|---|---|
| `src/core/snapshot/snapshot.engine.ts` | 50 | `Math.imul(h, 0x01000193)` (FNV-1a) | session 20260414 |
| `src/core/memory/immutable-memory.engine.ts` | 39 | `Math.imul(h, 0x01000193)` (FNV-1a) | session 20260414 |
| `src/governance/policy/policy-signature.engine.na` | 43 | `Math.imul(h1 ^ ch, 2654435761)` (Murmurhash) | session 20260414 |

**Status:** NOT_BYPASS — ready for crypto provider injection

#### §2.4.2 NEEDS FOLLOW-UP CONFIRM (NOT in 20260414 deep scan)

2 files with Math.imul that have NOT been documented as confirmed-placeholder:

| File | Line | Pattern | Action |
